\begin{align*}
\frac{9}{10}&=\frac{27}{30}\\
\frac{5}{6}&=\frac{25}{30}
\end{align*}
Now, I can add the fractions because they have the same denominator.
\begin{align*}
\frac{9}{10}+\frac{5}{6}&=\frac{27}{30}+\frac{25}{30}\\
&=\frac{52}{30}
\end{align*}
But, I am not finished yet. The fraction $\frac{52}{30}$ is not in its simplest form. I need to divide the numerator and denominator by their greatest common factor. The greatest common factor of $52$ and $30$ is $2$. So, I divide the numerator and denominator by $2$.
\begin{align*}
\frac{52}{30}&=\frac{26}{15}
\end{align*}
Therefore, $\frac{9}{10}+\frac{5}{6}=\boxed{\frac{26}{15}}$.
